After the addition of the **ultimate logout** feature there is an optional parameter called _ultimateLogout_ on the Logout OData action (_LogoutAction_ class). Except it is not truly optional now - if you omit it, you receive an _InvalidCastException_.

The reason is we do not handle this correctly in the **Execute** method of the **LogoutAction** class. In the beginning of the method we should handle if the parameter is **Type.Missing** instead of null or a bool value.

This should work, without the parameter:


    $.ajax({
         url: "/Odata.svc/('Root')/Logout",
         dataType: "json",
         type: 'POST',
         success: function () {
             console.log('Success!')
         }
    });

Please review these modifications. Consider the extension of the **RebuildIndexDirectly** method with the optional "**recursive**" parameter. With this the patch writer could use the whole re-indexing API.

The desired method:
void RebuildIndexDirectly(string path, IndexRebuildLevel level = IndexRebuildLevel.IndexOnly **, bool recursive = true**);
